task.summary: Default task
Refactored BootStrap into RidBootStrapService to make Bootstrap easier to maintain
Added service to create local directory copies of spreadsheet files in the .metridoc/files

Rewrote download methods in LibraryUnitController and TransactionController to download spreadsheets from .metridoc/files. Also wrote unit test for spreadSheetBootStrapService to ensure transfer of spreadsheets to local directory was successful
Refactored download() method of libraryUnitController and transactionController to abstract controller spreadsheetTransferMethodController

Refactored download() method of libraryUnitController and transactionController to service manageLibraryUnitSpreadsheets. Added a check to transferSpreadsheets() to prevent overwriting updated spreadsheets with older versions.

download() method in RidManageLibraryUnitSpreadsheetsService now properly finds and downloads file. Added a redirect back to index upon download failure in RidTransactionController. Removed special characters from method name in RidManageLibraryUnitSpreadsheetsServiceTest
Modified transferSpreadsheets() in RidManageLibraryUnitSpreadsheetsService to use input/output streams instead of renameTo in order to remove platform issues
Changed Transaction_list to Transaction_List in transfer spreadsheet testing in order to remove issues related to case sensitivity.
Removed unnecessary references to plugin metridoc-rid in views files. Updated "compile metridoc-core" to 0.54.4-SNAPSHOT in BuildConfig.groovy
Fixed spelling of duplicate in error messages. Re-inserted plugin references in view files to fix css import errors. Re-titled tabs in Transaction create form

Provided visual separation of Upload Spreadsheet and Download Spreadsheet in the spreadsheetUpload view. Removed list transactions tab. Removed unnecessary headers from create transaction and search transaction views
Changed download spreadsheet interface from a pop-up window to a pull-down menu. (from spreadsheetUpload.gsp)

Added a toggle button to switch between consultation transactions and instructional transactions. This information is stored in session scope. Currently, create, search, and spreadsheet upload views hide all forms and features while in instructional mode.

Refactored RidTransaction into RidConsTransaction and RidInsTransaction. Added test data for RidInsTransactions. Added new domain class RidLocation. Refactored parameter generation for RidBootStrapService into RidDataService. Implemented "search" action for RidInsTransaction

Implemented "create" and "show" for InstructionalTransactions. Enabled redirect back to previous action after toggling between consultation and instructional modes. Refactored the form template into formCons and formIns
Fixed TransactionControllerTests by adding a call to correctly set the transaction type
Added Consultation/Instructional toggle to TransactionAdmin controller and associated controllers and transaction management views (ridCourseSponsor/list.gsp, etc)
Added "Admin" to start of admin controllers and adjusted test names accordingly. Added login-requiring code to all controllers.
Fixed an error in saving InsTransaction templates. Added "reached character count" visual indicator to UserGoal box in InsTransaction create view; will refactor and add to appropriate input boxes.
Added toggle for switching between transaction functions and admin functions. Admin toggle is included in the toggles template.
Added tooltips for Transaction mode toggle and Administration mode toggle
Tweaked TransactionControllerTests syntax from session.setAttribute to controller.session.setAttribute to see if it will make Jenkins builds work.
Second tweak to try to get working Jenkins build

Refactored Admin controllers. Created AdminBaseController that has all methods used to add new members to RidSchool, RidRank, etc. Also updated the view pages accordingly. Next step is to refactor views.
Forgot to add AdminBaseController to svn

Yet another attempt to fix the TransactionControllerTest getSession bug in Jenkins. I altered the synax and lowered the method call below more of the setup code just in case something was being mocked in the wrong order.
Commented out problem tests in TransactionControllerTests. Added source and target lines to buildConfig

Factored out common code in AdminController view files and created _baseForm, _baseCreate, _baseEdit, and _baseList templates in ridAdminBase folder. Note that ridAdminLibraryUnit views have not been refactored due to the spreadsheet download functionality, and ridAdminDepartment has an unfactored list view.
Download spreadsheet bug fixed.
Small formatting changes
Small formatting changes
Some small rewordings of documentation files to make the language more formal.
Fixed download spreadsheet as Excel bug. Touched up documentation
Fixed downloading InsTransaction list as spreadsheet bug
Added tab and dropdown mode for the cons/ins switching button.
Fixed department icon bug. Department modal now properly shows the list of departments.
Set cons/ins switch mode to the dropdown box. Added select2 plugin which adds searchable dropdowns.
Added administration toggle to dropdown.
Fixed issue of default departments/libraryunits/etc not being added to the production version.
Made sure bootstrap won't try to add data that's already there
Changed version to 0.2.0-SNAPSHOT
Cosmetic changes to code styling
Added statistical reports to the admin view
Improved Admin/Transaction dropdown to include both modes and highlight the currently active mode in a manner consistent with the admin tab dropdown.

Bumped version to 0.1.2 to fix bugs. Issue where old pills layout appeared when logging in from link that wasn't the homepage fixed. Issue where typing in an entry for rank:other in the create forms threw an error. Statistics functionality present but set to development env only.
Statistics report remade to feature data tables with overview/monthly breakdown toggles and show all/show some functionality.
Make css/js imports use Resource plugin instead of r:external
